[{'comment_id': 938192203, 'comment_body': 'Hi @Faye-yufan I see that `.style("stroke", get_colour)` has been replaced by `select_style_fun(g_info, e)` which I guess works but is a bit confusing to me (previously it was clear that `get_colour` was responsible for stroke, but now it is not clear that `select_style_fun` is responsible for stroke -- does it also handle the alpha/opacity?). Did you trying modifying the `get_colour` function and that did not work for some reason? ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 4, 19, 49, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'tdhock', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 938200501, 'comment_body': "@tdhock yes, `select_style_fun` is responsible for both stroke and opacity. Since I'm still following the `ifSelectedElse` logic, which has to update selectors by get_colour/ get_colour_off two separate functions, I haven't tried modifying `get_colour` or getting rid of `ifSelectedElse`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 4, 20, 1, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Faye-yufan', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 938208679, 'comment_body': 'Will try modifying the get_colour function.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 4, 20, 12, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Faye-yufan', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 955409419, 'comment_body': 'instead of just g$geom / geom_point, can you please display g$classed or layer_name? (which should be something like geom1_point_scatter, that gives more information -- geom number and parent plot name)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 25, 20, 47, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'tdhock', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 955507795, 'comment_body': 'Yes, on it now', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 25, 23, 51, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Faye-yufan', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 956326899, 'comment_body': 'hi @Faye-yufan this should fix the unexpected test failure we observed